{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_018Jw7mbkMgrjkdBWZt648Hq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I fully understand. Both `app-producer` and `app-client` declare `app-queue`, but the producer uses `x-queue-mode=lazy` and the client uses no mode — so the client's declaration is rejected as inequivalent. The producer won the race and created the lazy queue. Each declares only once at startup (then loops publishing via the default exchange, which doesn't redeclare), so deleting the queue and letting the client recreate it (non-lazy) reconciles both without data-flow breakage.\n\nThe permission fix already made `ops-client` healthy — this queue conflict is the remaining blocker for `app-client`. Resolving it via RabbitMQ CLI:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4044,"cache_read_input_tokens":33821,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4044},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e2cf413-95c3-421c-8a24-785e54de87e8","uuid":"cf9376b3-a7a0-4982-aa31-b98f2becaed7","request_id":"req_011CcAcraXob8kX2emehDvC9"}
